&lt;p&gt;Conflicts:&lt;br/&gt;
	wicket-core/src/main/java/org/apache/wicket/ajax/form/OnChangeAjaxBehavior.java&lt;br/&gt;
	wicket-core/src/test/java/org/apache/wicket/ajax/form/OnChangeAjaxBehaviorTestPage_expected.html&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14153138" author="mgrigorov" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 13:02:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed it by using both &quot;inputchange&quot; and &quot;change&quot; for text field and area. And just &quot;change&quot; for everything else.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=svenmeier&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;svenmeier&quot;&gt;svenmeier&lt;/a&gt; I like this approach better than the one with the warning in 6.x and exception in 7.x because there is a way to support them without limitations.&lt;br/&gt;
Please reopen if you don&apos;t agree.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14153165" author="svenmeier" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 13:40:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m fine with this change now. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
